The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network for automatic map extraction using aerial images and trajectories. This involves computer vision (CV) techniques for image processing and machine learning (ML) techniques for data fusion. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves AI techniques for map extraction, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also involves robotics (RO) techniques for location-based services. Finally, the paper involves graph theory (GR) techniques for map representation.
